date: 2026-07-13
host: dev-32gb (16 cores, x86-64)
command: cargo run --release -p svtav1 --example perf_vs_c -- /tmp/perf2
settings: --lp 1, still-picture (--avif 1), CQP qindex 40, median of 3
c_reference: SvtAv1EncApp v4.2.0-rc (in-tree build, Release)
rust_build: release, no target-cpu=native (runtime dispatch as shipped)
commit: 5516423d2 (deblocking signaled + decoder-exact application live)
vs_baseline: perf_vs_c_2026-07-13.csv (c8821ef2e, pre-deblock) — rust_ms
  within run noise on every row (256p2 +0.9%, others -0.2%..-15%); the
  frame deblock pass (levels 1-3 at qindex<=63) is not measurable at these
  sizes. Ratio moves are dominated by C-side run variance.
caveats: C timings include app process startup (~constant ms, biases in C's
  favor at small sizes); rust timings are frame-encode only with warm buffers.
